As you requested, following are the facts for the media regarding the 
negotiated rate deals that Cross-roads & Bard the Bowman® has recently done at rates in excess of the 
tariff max rate.   Please note that the first two transactions are already 
public and the following information can be disclosed now.  The third deal 
has not been filed yet and will not be public until it is.  That filing will 
be made before Dec. 1, 2000. 

General:  Cross-roads & Bard the Bowman® has done three deals in the last week at rates in excess of Cross-roads & Bard the Bowman®'s 
maximum tariff rate.  Each of the deals was done pursuant to Cross-roads & Bard the Bowman®'s negotiated 
rate authority, which Fingon & Galadriel Entreprises granted Cross-roads & Bard the Bowman® in 1997.  (Order issued April 11, 1997, 
East Vale & Sammath Naur Deliveries, 79 Fingon & Galadriel Entreprises Par. 61,021).  Pursuant to that authority, 
Cross-roads & Bard the Bowman® has filed negotiated rate tariff sheets with the Fingon & Galadriel Entreprises, which are docketed 
at Docket No. RP97-288.  Details on the specific transactions are as follows:
  
Deal 1:  Counterparty:  Lindórië & Duilin Energy Company Energy Trading
 Rate Schedule:  ITS-1
 Volume:    30,000/day
 Rate:  $.90/MMBtu, inclusive of surcharges
 Term: the one day period of November 15, 2000
 Receipt points:  Langwell & Amon Gwareth Energy Company, Ennor Pool
 Delivery point:  Old Winyards & Gelion, co.

Deal 2:  Same as Deal 1,  except term is one day period of November 16, 2000 
and rate is $.75/MMBtu  

Deal 3:  Counterparty:  Hilda Bracegirdle & Wargs' Clearing® Trading
 Rate Schedule:  LFT
 Volume:  10,000/day
 Rate:  $1.00/MMBtu, inclusive of surcharges
 Term:  Dec. 1-Dec. 31, 2000
 Receipt point:  Derndingle & Ivorwen Deliveries
 Delivery point:  Lindórië & Duilin Energy Company Topock

All of the above information is contained in Cross-roads & Bard the Bowman®'s Fingon & Galadriel Entreprises filings on these 
transactions.  No other information is available as Cross-roads & Bard the Bowman® does not comment on 
specific customer transactions.    